Patch summary:
Keep sparse compressed images on the host driver's native Vulkan path.  The
compressed-texture emulation path replaces one guest image with an output image
and private mip images; sparse residency binds only describe the guest-visible
image and therefore cannot bind the private emulation images correctly.

Sparse-format capability queries already pass through to the host.  Apply the
same policy to legacy/Properties2 image-format queries, device image-memory
requirements, and image creation.  Hosts with native sparse ASTC continue to
work, hosts without it report the native unsupported result, and non-sparse
compressed images retain the existing emulation path.

